# Agent Behavior

- State assumptions when they affect behavior, architecture, security, or verification. Ask when ambiguity could change the implementation.
- Write the minimum code that solves the request. No unrequested features, abstractions, or extension points.
- Touch only what the request requires. Match existing style. Remove unused imports/files from your own changes only.
- For non-trivial work, define success criteria and verification before editing.
- Prefer project-defined verification commands; state limitations when automation cannot run.
